3EAfter%20I%20started%20staying%20at%20home%20with%20kids%2C%20my%20social%20life%20largely%20revolved%20around%20them.%20I%20started%20spending%20time%20with%20other%20parents%20I%20met%20at%20the%20playground%20or%20grabbing%20coffee%20with%20other%20parents%20who%20happened%20to%20enroll%20their%20kids%20in%20the%20same%20music%20class%20as%20mine.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20made%20some%20good%20friends%20this%20way.%20However%2C%20I%20regret%20not%20spending%20more%20time%20fostering%20the%20friendships%20I%20already%20had%2C%20especially%20with%20friends%20who%20didn't%20have%20kids.%20Without%20realizing%20it%2C%20my%20kids%20started%20dictating%20nearly%20every%20aspect%20of%20my%20social%20life.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20rare%20occasions%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalle-berry-motherhood-working-parents-identity-therapist-insights-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20went%20out%20without%20my%20kids%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20was%20always%20for%20a%20%26quot%3BMom's%20Night%20Out%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20conversation%20largely%20centered%20on%20children.%20Now%20that%20three%20of%20my%20kids%20are%20teenagers%2C%20I%20am%20no%20longer%20a%20part%20of%20their%20social%20lives.%20They%20hang%20out%20with%20friends%20and%20go%20to%20lessons%20without%20me.%20That's%20how%20it%20should%20be%2C%20but%20I%20acutely%20feel%20the%20loss%20of%20the%20friendships%20I%20let%20slip%20when%20they%20were%20younger.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe7d4331-570d-42c7-ab05-ac5203891cbe%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20should%20have%20fostered%20my%20own%20interests%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20used%20to%20be%20someone%20with%20hobbies.%20I%20would%20hike%2C%20read%2C%20take%20photos%2C%20and%20even%20dabbled%20in%20knitting.%20After%20having%20kids%2C%20my%20hobbies%20fell%20by%20the%20wayside%20one%20by%20one.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHiking%20was%20easy%20with%20babies%20but%20harder%20with%20toddlers.%20My%20toddlers%20were%20willing%20to%20be%20photography%20subjects%2C%20but%20my%20tweens%20were%20not.%20Many%20nights%2C%20I%20was%20too%20exhausted%20to%20read%20more%20than%20a%20page%20or%20two.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20became%20completely%20subsumed%20by%20my%20kids'%20interests.%20It%20was%20fun%2C%20but%20my%20deep%20knowledge%20of%20Lego%2C%20Marvel%2C%20and%20American%20Girl%20dolls%20is%20largely%20useless%20now%20that%20my%20kids%20are%20teens.%20I%20could%20fill%20some%20of%20the%20time%20I%20have%20to%20myself%20now%20that%20my%20kids%20are%20older%20with%20hobbies.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20pick%20up%20where%20I%20left%20off%20except%20for%20reading.%20If%20I%20had%20continued%20to%20foster%20my%20interests%20outside%20kids%2C%20even%20in%20a%20small%20way%2C%20I%20would%20have%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20who%20I%20am%20outside%20of%20a%20mother.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227516d755-0f5f-4635-af0c-332e96e1023c%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20should%20have%20taken%20better%20care%20of%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20having%20kids%2C%20I%20worked%20out%20daily%20and%20enjoyed%20preparing%20dinner%20every%20night.%20I%20occasionally%20treated%20myself%20to%20massages.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20having%20kids%2C%20I%20was%20obsessive%20about%20their%20health%20but%20let%20my%20own%20fall%20by%20the%20wayside.%20I%20wouldn't%20hesitate%20to%20take%20my%20kids%20to%20the%20doctor%20for%20a%20sniffle%2C%20but%20I%20skipped%20my%20own%20annual%20physical%20for%20years.%20I%20stopped%20going%20to%20the%20gym%20because%20I%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20work%20it%20into%20my%20schedule.%20I%20enrolled%20my%20kids%20in%20sports%20to%20keep%20them%20active%20but%20