-bust-alleged-prostitution-ring-targeting-tourists%2Famp_articleshow%2F117944650.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ftokyo-police-bust-alleged-prostitution-ring-targeting-tourists%2Famp_articleshow%2F117944650.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22El%20Salvador%20Offers%20To%20Jail%20Deportees%20From%20US%20Of%20Any%20Nationality%2C%20But%20At%20A%20Cost%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEl%20Salvador%20has%20offered%20to%20incarcerate%20American%20convicts%20and%20illegal%20migrants%20of%20any%20nationality%20deported%20from%20the%20United%20States%20at%20Latin%20America's%20largest%20maximum%20security%20prison.%20But%2C%20Salvadoran%20President%20Nayib%20Bukele's%20proposal%20comes%20with%20a%20price%20tag%20and%20legal%20challenges%20--ones%20that%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20administration%20is%20considering%20to%20tackle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20meeting%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20on%20Monday%2C%20Bukele%20offered%20to%20lock%20up%20convicts%20%26quot%3Bof%20any%20nationality%26quot%3B%2C%20sent%20by%20the%20United%20States%2C%20at%20the%20facility%20known%20as%20CECOT%2C%20where%20prisoners%20live%20crammed%20in%20windowless%20cells%2C%20sleeping%20on%20metal%20beds%20with%20no%20mattress%2C%20forbidden%20from%20having%20visitors%20and%20kept%20under%20watch%2024%20hours%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIron-fisted%20Bukele%2C%20who%20enjoys%20sky-high%20approval%20ratings%20for%20his%20sweeping%20crackdown%20on%20violent%20gangs%2C%20said%20that%20El%20Salvador%20wanted%20to%20give%20the%20United%20States%20a%20chance%20to%20%26quot%3Boutsource%20part%20of%20its%20prison%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Considering%20El%20Salvador's%20Proposal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20on%20Tuesday%20backed%20El%20Salvador's%20offer%20despite%20clear%20legal%20problems%20with%20such%20an%20outsourcing%20under%20American%20law.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20had%20the%20legal%20right%20to%20do%20it%2C%20I%20would%20do%20it%20in%20a%20heartbeat%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20no%20different%20than%20our%20prison%20system%2C%20except%20it%20would%20be%20a%20lot%20less%20expensive%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20a%20great%20deterrent%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20would%20negotiate%20payment%2C%20which%20would%20decrease%20costs%20for%20the%20United%20States%20but%20help%20fund%20El%20Salvador's%20own%20mass%20incarceration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20that%20shipping%20criminals%20to%20El%20Salvador%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20small%20fee%20compared%20to%20what%20we%20pay%20to%20private%20prisons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20they%20could%20keep%20them%2C%20because%20these%20people%20are%20never%20going%20to%20be%20any%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20top%20envoy%20Rubio%2C%20who%20met%20Bukele%20on%20Monday%2C%20also%20said%20the%20Trump%20administration%20would%20review%20the%20proposal%20but%20acknowledged%20legal%20issues.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20have%20to%20study%20it%20on%20our%20end.%20There%20are%20obviously%20legalities%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20Rubio%20told%20reporters%20a%20day%20afterwards%20in%20Costa%20Rica%2C%20where%20he%20headed%20after%20El%20Salvador.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20constitution%2C%20we%20have%20all%20sorts%20of%20things%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20very%20generous%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20Rubio%20said.%20He%20welcomed%20the%20offer%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%20one's%20ever%20made%20an%20offer%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EEl%20Salvador's%20Offer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20Bukele's%20offer%2C%20Rubia%20said%20apart%20from%20Salvadoran%20deportees%20who%20illegally%20entered%20the%20US%2C%20El%20Salvador%20will%20also%20%26quot%3Baccept%20for%20deportation%20any%20illegal%20alien%20in%20the%20United%20States%20who%20is%20a%20criminal%20from%20any%20nationality%2C%20be%20they%20MS-13%20or%20Tren%20de%20Aragua%20and%20house%20them%20in%20his%20jails%26quot%3B--%20referring%20to%20two%20notorious%20transnational%20gangs%20with%20members%20from%20El%20Salvador%20and%20Venezuela.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Bukele%20%26quot%3Bhas%20offered%20to%20house%20in%20his%20jails%20dangerous%20American%20criminals%20in%20custody%20in%20our%20country%2C%20including%20those%20of%20US%20citizenship%20and%20legal%20residents%2C%26quot%3B%20Rubio%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Constitution%20forbids%20%26quot%3Bcruel%20and%20unusual%20punishment%26quot%3B%20and%20promises%20due%20process.%20There%20is%20little%20precedent%20in%20modern%20times%20for%20a%20democratic%20country%20to%20send%20its%20own%20citizens%20to%20foreign%20prisons.%20Moreover%2C%20US%20citizens%20who%20were%20born%20in%20America%20enjoy%20legal%20protection%20from%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20some%20cases%20where%20naturalised%20citizens%20-%20those%20who%20were%20not%20born%20in%20the%20US%20and%20who%20obtained%20US%20citizenship%20after%20birth%20through%20a%20legal%20process%20-%20can%20have%20their%20citizenship%20revoked.%20This%20generally%20happens%20in%20the%20case%20where%20the%20person%20in%20question%20used%20fraud%20to%20obtain%20citizenship%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20questions%20around%20the%20legality%20of%20such%20a%20move%2C%20any%20effort%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20deport%20incarcerated%20US%20nationals%20to%20another%20country%20is%20likely%20to%20face%20significant%20legal%20pushback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20CECOT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEl%20Salvador's%20Terrorism%20Confinement%20Center%2C%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20CECOT%2C%20is%20the%20country's%20largest%20prison%20which%20opened%20in%202023%2C%20with%20a%20maximum%20capacity%20of%2040%2C000%20inmates.%20It%20is%20made%20up%20of%20eight%20sprawling%20pavilions.%20Its%20cells%20hold%2065%20to%2070%20prisoners%20each%2C%20who%20do%20not%20receive%20visits%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Associated%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrisoners%20in%20boxer%20shorts%20are%20reportedly%20marched%20into%20prison%20yards%20and%20made%20to%20sit%20nearly%20atop%20each%20other.%20They%20are%20packed%20into%20cells%20without%20enough%20bunks%20for%20everyone.%20Moreover%2C%20there%20are%20no%20programs%20preparing%20these%20prisoners%20to%20return%20to%20society%20after%20their%20sentences--%20no%20workshops%20or%20educational%20programs--%20as%20they%20are%20never%20allowed%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBukele's%20iron-fisted%20rule%20has%20been%20greatly%20credited%20for%20reducing%20gang%20violence%20in%20the%20Central%20American%20country%20since%20launching%20a%20sweeping%20crackdown%20in%202022%20that%20has%20seen%20the%20imprisonment%20of%20over%2080%2C000%20people.%20But%20while%20the%20crime%20rate%20in%20what%20was%20once%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20violent%20countries%20has%20fallen%2C%20the%20treatment%20of%20those%20imprisoned%20has%20triggered%20outrage%20among%20human%20rights%20organizations%20who%20call%20El%20Salvador's%20prisons%20inhumane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Crackdown%20on%20Illegal%20Immigration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20as%20part%20of%20his%20administration's%20crackdown%20on%20illegal%20immigration%2C%20Trump%20has%20already%20announced%20that%20the%20United%20States%20will%20hold%20migrants%20at%20the%20notorious%20Guantanamo%20military%20detention%20facility%20in%20Cuba%20that%20was%20opened%20in%20January%202002.%20But%20that%20prison%20is%20built%20on%20a%20US%20naval%20base%20leased%20from%20Havana%20under%20a%20treaty%20dating%20back%20to%201903.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20detention%20facility%20was%20set%20up%20after%20the%2011%20September%202001%20attacks%20to%20deal%20with%20prisoners%20who%20were%20termed%20%26quot%3Benemy%20combatants%26quot%3B%20and%20denied%20many%20US%20legal%20rights.%20Democratic%20presidents%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20Joe%20Biden%20both%20sought%20to%20close%20the%20facility%2C%20but%20Congress%20has%20opposed%20efforts%20to%20shut%20Guantanamo%20and%20it%20remains%20open%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio's%20visit%20this%20week%2C%20Washington%20had%20touted%20El%20Salvador%20as%20a%20possible%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20third%20country%26quot%3B%20for%20expelled%20migrants%20whose%20countries%20do%20not%20accept%20US%20deportation%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20United%20States%20began%20flying%20detained%20migrants%20to%20the%20notorious%20military%20base%20in%20Cuba%2C%20where%20hundreds%20of%20terrorism%20suspects%20were%20held%20for%20years%20after%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%2C%20many%20without%20formal%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738746120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fqkjsv5ng_el-salvadors-cecot-afp_625x300_05_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fel-salvador-offers-to-jail-deportees-from-us-of-any-nationality-but-at-a-cost-7639505%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22El%20Salvador%20has%20offered%20to%20incarcerate%20American%20convicts%20and%20illegal%20migrants%20of%20any%20nationality%20deported%20from%20the%20United%20States%20at%20Latin%20America's%20largest%20maximum%20security%20prison.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fel-salvador-offers-to-jail-deportees-from-us-of-any-nationality-but-at-a-cost-7639505%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Abhishek%20Sharma%20jumps%2038%20places%20to%202nd%20in%20T20I%20rankings%22%2C%22