6quot%3BThe%20US%20will%20take%20over%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20and%20we%20will%20do%20a%20job%20with%20it%20too.%20We'll%20own%20it%20and%20be%20responsible%20for%20dismantling%20all%20of%20the%20dangerous%20unexploded%20bombs%20and%20other%20weapons%20on%20the%20site%2C%20level%20the%20site%2C%20and%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20destroyed%20buildings%2C%20level%20it%20out%2C%20create%20an%20economic%20development%20that%20will%20supply%20unlimited%20numbers%20of%20jobs%20and%20housing%20for%20the%20people%20of%20the%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Donald%20Trump%20said%20in%20his%20opening%20remarks%20at%20the%20White%20House%20press%20conference%20with%20Israel's%20Natyenhyahu%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20US%20officials%20are%20framing%20his%20call%20to%20permanently%20%26quot%3Bresettle%26quot%3B%20all%20Palestinians%20out%20of%20Gaza%20as%20a%20humanitarian%20gesture%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20alternative%20for%20people%20living%20there%20because%20Gaza%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bdemolition%20site%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20has%20for%20decades%20backed%20a%20two-state%20solution%20between%20the%20Israelis%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20would%20create%20a%20state%20for%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20Israeli-occupied%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20alongside%20Israel.%20Trump%20was%20asked%20if%20under%20him%20Washington%20no%20longer%20supported%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20mean%20anything%20about%20a%20two%20state%20or%20one%20state%20or%20any%20other%20state%2C%20it%20means%20that%20..%20we%20want%20to%20give%20people%20a%20chance%20at%20life%20...%20because%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20has%20been%20a%20hell%20hole%20for%20people%20living%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20without%20directly%20answering%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Will%20Happen%20To%20Palestinians%20Living%20In%20Gaza%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20President%20said%20Washington%20would%20ask%20other%20neighbouring%20countries%20to%20take%20in%20Palestinians%20displaced%20from%20Gaza.%20Since%20January%2025%2C%20he%20has%20repeatedly%20asked%20Egypt%20and%20Jordan%20to%20do%20so%2C%20a%20proposal%20rejected%20by%20them%20and%20other%20Arab%20states.%20Gaza's%20population%20before%20the%20war%20was%202.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20we%20should%20go%20to%20other%20countries%20of%20interest%20with%20humanitarian%20hearts%2C%20and%20there%20are%20many%20of%20them%20that%20want%20to%20do%20this%20and%20build%20various%20domains%20that%20will%20ultimately%20be%20occupied%20by%20the%201.8%20million%20Palestinians%20living%20in%20Gaza%2C%20ending%20the%20death%20and%20destruction%20and%20frankly%2C%20bad%20luck.%20This%20could%20be%20paid%20for%20by%20neighbouring%20countries%20of%20great%20wealth%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20Will%20Live%20In%20Gaza%20Rebuilt%20By%20Trump%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20envision%20world%20people%20living%20there%2C%20the%20world's%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20when%20asked%20who%20did%20he%20envision%20living%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPalestinians%20also%2C%20Palestinians%20will%20live%20there%2C%20many%20people%20will%20live%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%20without%20elaborating%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20Trump%20Planning%20To%20Send%20US%20Troops%20To%20Execute%20His%20Plan%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20Washington%20would%20send%20US%20troops%20to%20Gaza%20under%20his%20proposal%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20do%20what%20is%20necessary.%20If%20it's%20necessary%2C%20we'll%20do%20that.%20We're%20going%20to%20take%20over%20that%20piece.%20We're%20going%20to%20develop%20it%2C%20create%20thousands%20and%20thousands%20of%20jobs%2C%20and%20it'll%20be%20something%20that%20the%20entire%20Middle%20East%20can%20be%20very%20proud%20of.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20Can%20US%20Execute%20Trump's%20Plan%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20law%20strictly%20prohibits%20any%20attempt%20to%20forcibly%20transfer%20a%20population.%20Gaza%20was%20already%20home%20to%20Palestinians%20who%20fled%20or%20were%20forced%20out%20of%20their%20homes%20in%20the%20wars%20surrounding%20Israel's%20creation.%20Mr%20Trump's%20proposed%20plan%2C%20if%20executed%2C%20would%20involve%20forcing%20these%20Palestinians%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20Arab%20world%20or%20even%20beyond.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20proposal%20also%20completely%20removes%20any%20possibility%20of%20a%20future%20two-state%20solution%2C%20and%20would%20likely%20be%20rejected%20by%20Palestinians%20and%20the%20Arab%20world%20as%20an%20expulsion%20plan%20aimed%20at%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArab%20leaders%20have%20already%20categorically%20rejected%20the%20US%20President's%20ideas.%20In%20a%20statement%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Qatar%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20and%20the%20Arab%20League%20said%20that%20such%20a%20move%20could%20%26quot%3Bthreaten%20the%20region's%20stability%2C%20risk%20expanding%20the%20conflict%2C%20and%20undermine%20prospects%20for%20peace%20and%20coexistence%20among%20its%20peoples%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20under%20the%20Geneva%20Conventions%2C%20forced%20removal%20of%20the%20population%20could%20be%20permitted%20in%20specific%20situations%20like%20evacuating%20a%20civilian%20population%20when%20their%20security%20is%20at%20risk%20or%20due%20to%20imperative%20military%20reasons%2C%20and%20also%20when%20moving%20prisoners%20of%20war%20out%20of%20combat%20zones%20to%20internment%20facilities%2C%20provided%20the%20proper%20conditions%20are%20met.%20However%2C%20the%20key%20principle%20of%20such%20removals%20must%20be%20jus